          "outputSpecification": "{}",
          "type": "BO_FUNCTION",
          "diagram": {
            "x": 5000,
            "y": 7648
          }
        },
        {
          "aiAppOutputSpecification": {
            "dataDisplay": {
              "layouts": [
                "ORA_LAYOUT_MULTIRECORD"
              ],
              "enableActions": true,
              "enableCommunications": false,
              "customNotes": "## DIRECTIVE\n\nYour sole purpose is to transform the provided succession, salary, and performance data into a valid `oraInfoDisplay` structure using the `multiRecordWidget`.\n\nRender the output as a human-readable dashboard with exactly two sequential sections:\n\n\n## ROOT CONFIGURATION\n\n* `title`: Do not include any title.\n* `description`: Generate a short, non-repetitive summary of the matched employee records (maximum 50 words)\n\n---\n\n\n### Field Extraction\n\n* `Annual Salary` → from `SalaryInfo.items[].AnnualSalary`\n* `Quartile` → from `SalaryInfo.items[].QuartileMeaning`\n* `Quintile` → from `SalaryInfo.items[].QuintileMeaning`\n* `Performance` → from `PerfomanceInfo.items[].PerfomanceLevel`\n\n### Record Matching\n\n* Match records using `AssignmentId` between `Data` and `SalaryInfo`\n\n---\n\n## DISPLAY FIELDS (STRICT)\n\nInclude **ONLY** the following fields in the Details section:\n\n* Name(**highlighted**)\n* Job\n* Annual Salary\n* Quartile\n* Quintile\n* Performance\n* Risk of Loss\n* Impact of Loss\n* Succession Plan Count\n\n---\n\n## READINESS COLUMNS (MANDATORY)\n\nAlways display **FOUR separate readiness columns**:\n\n1. Ready Now\n2. Ready in 1–2 yrs\n3. Ready in 3–4 yrs\n4. No Readiness\n\n### Rules:\n\n* Always include all four columns\n* Never merge categories\n* If no candidates exist → display: **\"0 candidates\"**\n* Format:\n  **{count} candidates: {names}**\n* If count = 0 → omit names\n\n---\n\n### **Zero Succession Override Rule (Critical)**\n\n* If `Succession Plan Count = 0`:\n\n  * Set all readiness categories to exactly:\n\n    * **Ready Now → 0 candidates**\n    * **Ready in 1–2 yrs → 0 candidates**\n    * **Ready in 3–4 yrs → 0 candidates**\n    * **No Readiness → 0 candidates**\n  * Do NOT display any names in these fields\n  * Ignore any candidate data if present (data inconsistency safeguard)\n\n-------\n\n## DISPLAY FORMAT RULES\n\n* Render output strictly as:\n\n  * **Summary section**\n  * **Details section**\n\n### Details Section Requirements:\n\n* Must be a **two-column table only**\n* Columns:\n\n  * **Property**\n  * **Value**\n* Do NOT add extra columns\n* Do NOT display any IDs\n* Keep formatting clean and human-readable\n\n---\n\n## VISUAL / COLOR RULES\n\n* Apply colored badges ONLY for:\n\n  * High → alert (Red)\n  * Medium → warning (Orange)\n  * Low → success (Green)\n\n* Do NOT apply badges to:\n  \n  * Performance\n  * Person names\n  * Assignment names\n\n---\n\n## DATA INTEGRITY RULES\n\n* Do NOT invent missing values\n* If data is unavailable → use **N/A** or leave blank\n* Do NOT include links or extra fields\n\n---\n\n## ACTION LOGIC\n\n* Do NOT include any `action` property\n* Do NOT include footer buttons\n\nIf actions are introduced later:\n\n* Use `ora.Invoke(\"command\")`\n* Or `ora.Invoke(\"command\", \"{contextData}\")` where context includes only necessary identifiers\n\n---\n\n## OUTPUT CONSTRAINTS\n\n* Do NOT display any separate visible title beyond the defined structure\n* Summary must always be present\n* Output must remain concise, structured, and strictly follow all rules above\n\n** FINAL OUTPUT RULE:\n   * Return ONLY a single <oraInfoDisplay> XML block and NOTHING ELSE.\n   * No trailing text. No leading text. No explanations."
            }
          },
          "metadata": {
            "name": "Generate Succession Details For Person"
